## Git Commit After Task Completion

After setting task status to "done", automatically:
1. Check if git repository exists
2. Collect changed files via `git status --porcelain`
3. Generate commit message from task data (ID, title, description)
4. Execute `git add .` and `git commit` with generated message

**Commit message format:**
```
feat(task-{id}): {task_title}

{task_description}

Changes:
- {list of changed files}

Task: {id} - {title}
Status: done
```

**Non-blocking**: Workflow continues even if git is unavailable or no changes exist.

See [git_commit.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/taskmaster/git_commit.mdc) for detailed implementation.

